  "prompt": "What is best free one page theme for WordPress?",
  "response": "Choosing the \"best\" free one-page theme for WordPress can be subjective, as it often depends on individual needs and preferences, such as design elements, customization options, and the specific features required. However, several free one-page themes are highly recommended by users and experts in the WordPress community. Here are a few notable ones:\n\n1. **Hestia**\n   - Hestia is a modern one-page theme that is highly customizable, making it suitable for startups, small businesses, or personal portfolios. It offers smooth scrolling, a clean and stylish design, and compatibility with popular page builders like Elementor.\n\n2. **OnePress**\n   - OnePress is a robust theme that provides a professional look for agencies, businesses, and freelancers. It includes various sections, such as services, testimonials, and portfolio, all structured in a one-page design.\n\n3. **Zerif Lite**\n   - Zerif Lite is another popular one-page theme that has a clean and minimalistic design. It's ideal for small business websites, agencies, and personal portfolios. It features smooth scrolling and responsive layouts.\n\n4. **Sydney**\n   - Sydney is a powerful business theme that provides a stunning one-page layout. It offers plenty of customization options, such as access to all Google Fonts, full-color control, layout options, and more. It's also compatible with Elementor.\n\n5. **Shapely**\n   - Shapely is excellent for those looking to create a landing page, portfolio, or personal website. It offers a clean and modern design with responsive sections for services, testimonials, portfolios, and more.\n\n6. **Neve**\n   - Neve is designed to be fast and lightweight, making it perfect for one-page designs. It offers easy customization options and seamless integration with WooCommerce and popular page builders.\n\n7. **Illdy**\n   - Illdy is a multipurpose theme that features a full-screen one-page layout. It's suitable for businesses, landing pages, and portfolios. It includes various customization options and responsive design elements.\n\nEach of these themes has unique features and design elements, so you might want to explore them to see which one best fits your needs. Additionally, checking out user reviews and ratings can help you make a more informed decision.",
